taxonomyNotes: Was proposed as a new name for the species previously known as C. melanocephalus, which was later reverted. Both changes are controversial but it appears that recent literature and the IUCN has favored the decision to use C. hosomi rather than C. melanocephalus, which is now used for the species previously known as C. oukary. Cacajao ayresi has been included under C. hosomi as a subspecies but is recognized as distinct in recent literature and the IUCN, although the distinctions between the two are low and they may be conspecific.
